Section 1051 of the Lanham Act (15 U.S.C. §1051) – Application for Registration:

> (a) Every person claiming a right to a trademark may apply to the Director for registration of the mark, provided that the person has either used the mark in commerce or intends to use the mark in commerce.
> (b) The application shall contain:
>   (1) the name and address of the applicant;
>   (2) a clear depiction of the mark;
>   (3) a statement of the goods and/or services associated with the mark, identified by class;
>   (4) a declaration that the applicant either has used the mark in commerce or has a bona fide intention to use the mark in commerce;
>   (5) any required fees.
> (c) The Director may refuse registration if the mark is merely descriptive, generic, or likely to cause confusion with an existing registration.
